CITATION: 1983 AIR 1002 1983 SCR (3) 600 1983 SCC (4) 197 1983 SCALE (2)91 
ACT:
 Evidence-Circurmstantial evidence-Several circumstances supported by medical evidence lead to the only conclusion that the deceased was murdered in a most brutal and heinous fashion and then hung by rope by the accused so as to give an appearance of a case of suicide - Conviction and sentence for the offence of murder should be confirmed.
 
